Claims WHAT IS CLAIMED IS: 1. A system for classifying text as a question or a request, comprising: a linguistic engine configured to: access an utterance comprising at least one word; generate a parse tree for the utterance, wherein the parse tree comprises at least one terminal node comprising a word type, wherein each terminal node represents a word or phrase of the utterance; and apply, to the parse tree, one or more linguistic templates comprising one or more word types; and a rule engine configured to generate one or more match results obtained from the linguistic engine and determine a classification of the text by applying rules comprising: (i) responsive to determining a linguistic template match, classifying the utterance as a request, (ii) responsive to determining that the utterance comprises an imperative verb as a first word of the utterance, classifying the utterance as a request, (iii) responsive to identifying, in the utterance, one or more predefined request keywords, classifying the utterance as a request, and (iv) responsive to identifying, in the utterance, one or more predefined question keywords, classifying the utterance as a question, wherein the system is further configured, based on the classification, to send a message to a user device or adjust a configuration of an external device. 2. The system of claim 1 , wherein the rules further comprise (v) responsive to failing to identify the utterance as a question or a request, classifying the utterance as unknown. 3. The system of claim 1 , wherein the linguistic template comprises a first person pronoun and a noun. 4. The system of claim 1 , wherein the rules further comprise (v) responsive to determining that the utterance comprises a question prefix in a first word position, classifying the utterance as a question. 5. The system of claim 1 , wherein the one or more predefined question words comprise mental verbs. 6. The system of claim 1 , wherein the rules further comprise (v) responsive to determining that the utterance comprises a request suffix at in a last word position of the utterance, classifying the utterance as a request. 7. The system of claim 1 , wherein the rules further comprise (v) responsive to determining that the utterance comprises transaction verb, classifying the utterance as a request. 8. The system of claim 1 , wherein the linguistic engine is configured to, prior to determining the parse tree, removing one or more stop words from the utterance. 9. A method of using a classification model to classify utterances as questions or requests, the method comprising: accessing an utterance of text, wherein the utterance comprises at least one word; generating a parse tree for the utterance, wherein the parse tree comprises least one terminal node comprising a word type, wherein each terminal node represents a word or phrase of the utterance; determining a classification of the utterance by applying a classification model to the parse tree, the applying comprising: determining, for the parse tree, a first similarity score indicating a first match between the utterance and training classes identified as questions, and determining, for the parse tree, a second similarity score indicating a second match between the utterance and training classes identified as requests; receiving, from the classification model, a classification of the utterance, wherein the classification of the utterance is (i) based on a similarity score for the determined class being higher than other similarity scores or is (ii) unknown. 10. The method of claim 9, further comprising: 

 accessing a set of training data comprising a set of training data pairs, wherein each training data pair comprises text and an expected classification, and wherein the set of training data includes both (i) a first training data pair that comprises a question and (ii) a second training data pair comprises a request; and training a classification model by iteratively: providing one of the training data pairs to the classification model; receiving, from the classification model, a determined classification; calculating a loss function by calculating a difference between the determined classification and the expected classification; and adjusting internal parameters of the classification model to minimize the loss function. 1 1. The method of claim 9, wherein the classification is the classification that comprises the highest similarity to the utterance. 12. A method of classifying an utterance as a question or a request, the method comprising: accessing an utterance of text, wherein the utterance comprises at least one word; generating a parse tree for the utterance, wherein the parse tree comprises at least one terminal node comprising a word type, wherein each terminal node represents a word of the utterance; and performing one or more operations from a set of operations comprising: (i) responsive to determining that a first terminal node of the parse tree comprises an imperative verb, classifying the utterance as a request, and (ii) responsive to classifying, in the parse tree, one or more predefined question keywords, classifying the utterance as a question. 13. The method of claim 12, wherein the operations further comprise: applying, to the parse tree, one or more linguistic templates comprising one or more word types; and responsive to determining, a linguistic template match, classifying the utterance as a request. 14. The method of claim 12, wherein the word types comprise a pronoun in a first person tense and a noun. 15. The method of claim 12, wherein the operations further comprise responsive to failing to identify the utterance as a question or a request, classifying the utterance as unknown. 16. The method of claim 12, wherein the operations further comprise (iii) responsive to classifying, in the utterance, one or more predefined request keywords, classifying the utterance as a request. 17. The method of claim 12, wherein the operations further comprise (iii) determining that the utterance comprises a question prefix, classifying the utterance as a question. 18. The method of claim 12, wherein the one or more predefined question words comprise mental verbs. 19. The method of claim 12, wherein the one or more predefined request keywords comprise a transaction suffix or a transaction verb. 20. A system comprising: a computer-readable medium storing non-transitory computer-executable program instructions; and a processing device communicatively coupled to the computer-readable medium for executing the non-transitory computer-executable program instructions, wherein executing the non-transitory computer-executable program instructions configures the processing device to perform operations comprising: accessing an utterance of text, wherein the utterance comprises at least one word; generating a parse tree for the utterance, wherein the parse tree comprises at least one terminal node comprising a word type, wherein each terminal node represents a word or phrase of the utterance; 

 determining a classification of the utterance by applying a classification model to the parse tree, the applying comprising: determining, for the parse tree, a first similarity score indicating a first match between the utterance and training classes identified as utterances, and determining, for the parse tree, a second similarity score indicating a second match between the utterance and training classes identified as requests; receiving, from the classification model, a classification of the utterance, wherein the classification of the utterance is either (i) based on a similarity score for the determined class being higher than other similarity scores or is (ii) unknown.
